Subject: rPSA-2008-0052-1 kernel

rPath Security Advisory: 2008-0052-1
Published: 2008-02-12
Products:
    rPath Linux 1
    rPath Appliance Platform Linux Service 1

Rating: Critical
Exposure Level Classification:
    Local Root Deterministic Privilege Escalation
Updated Versions:
    kernel=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1-vmware/2.6.22.18-0.1-1
    kernel=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/2.6.22.18-0.1-1
    kernel=rap.rpath.com@...th:linux-1/2.6.22.18-1-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-2237

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-0600

Description:
    Previous versions of the Linux kernel package are vulnerable to
    a local user privilege escalation vulnerability that is widely
    publicized and being actively exploited.  All users are encouraged
    to update their systems immediately.
    
    This vulnerability was introduced in the 2.6.17 kernel; the
    kernels on the conary.rpath.com@rpl:1-xen label are not affected.
    
    A system reboot is required to resolve this vulnerability.

http://wiki.rpath.com/Advisories:rPSA-2008-0052

